body:
While troubleshooting #172 I set up this config file:

```JSON
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "server1": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer rutabaga"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Replace `rutabaga` with your GitHub PAT (or leave it, the error is the same.)

Run `mcp-cli tools --config-file /tmp/api-github.yaml`

The output is big but seems to start with

```
ERROR    MCP OAuth authentication failed for server1: Client error '404 Not Found' for url 'https://api.githubcopilot.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server'
```

Not all MCP servers support OAuth.
